A fourth and final mineworker trapped at the Tau Lekoa mine in Orkney has been confirmed dead. ORKNEY - A fourth and final mineworker trapped at the Tau Lekoa mine in Orkney has been confirmed dead. The body was found by the recovery team on Saturday night. READ: Three miners' bodies recovered from Tau Lekoa mine Five workers became trapped after seismic events caused rockfalls at the mine on Friday afternoon. A seriously injured miner was brought to the surface on the same day. The bodies of three mineworkers were brought to the surface on Saturday. READ: Miners trapped underground in North West NUM regional secretary Masibulele Naki said the recovery teams are struggling to reach the mineworker's body. In 2017, miners were trapped after a rockfall at the mine.